                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/74.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that, although rumors of war continue to circulate and
                    considerable uncertainty and anxiety prevail, he is still hopeful that recourse
                    to arms will be avoided, as the leaders of the constitutional party continue to
                    act in the most conservative manner and are evidently doing everything in their
                    power to calm the bellicose spirit of the army, much to the discomfiture of the
                    reactionaries.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
